  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Communities to Conserve Dry Forests</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With only 2% remaining, Peru&apos;s dry forests are one of the most endangered ecosystems in the world. Native trees are heavily logged yet are crucial to the survival and wellbeing of local communities and endangered wildlife. Located on Peru&apos;s northern coast, this project will work with low-income farmers and community members to reforest this threatened landscape. Local people will be trained on how to restore and sustainably manage dry forests in ways that boost their income and conserve habitat.</narrative>
  </description>
